    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nI've been using helix for a while and found it helpful that `u` can restore the last selected content.\r\n\r\nI tried to reproduce it in neovim with this code:\r\n```lua\r\n    [\"u\"] = function ()\r\n        local spos = api.nvim_buf_get_mark(0, '<')\r\n\r\n        api.nvim_command(\"normal! u\")\r\n\r\n        local cpos = api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0)\r\n\r\n        if cpos[1] == spos[1] and cpos[2] == spos[2] then\r\n            enter_select()\r\n            api.nvim_command(\"normal! gv\")\r\n        end\r\n    end,\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut it will only resume the latest visual selecting content. Earlier selected content cannot be restored with `gv`\r\n\r\nor enhance `1gv` `2gv` `3gv` can resume the earlier selected content might be a good idea?\r\n\r\n\r\nso I'm wondering if the neovim can support this natively.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/97107165/223972251-b5356fff-dcc4-4572-b66e-6c196791ab11.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
